# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AI assistant tooling (local-only, mirrors stateful-y/yohou)
#
# Patterns are anchored with a leading "/" so they apply to this repo's root
# only. Unanchored patterns match at any depth and would silently swallow
# product files under template/ (e.g. a future template/.claude/).
#
# Deliberately NOT listed: .github/skills/** and .github/copilot-instructions.md
# are tracked here, and gitignore does not affect tracked files. Listing them
# would be inert. Untrack them first if they should become local-only.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Copilot-side openspec artifacts. openspec installs Claude-native equivalents
# under .claude/commands/opsx/, so these are redundant duplicates. Ignoring them
# also keeps rumdl (which honours .gitignore) off files openspec generates.
/.github/prompts/
/.github/skills/openspec-*/

# AI Assistant Instructions
/CLAUDE.md
/CLAUDE_INSTRUCTIONS.md
/.claude.md
/claude-instructions.md
/claude-config.md
/claude-prompt.md
/reviews/

# GitHub Copilot
/COPILOT.md
/COPILOT_INSTRUCTIONS.md
/.copilot.md
/copilot-instructions.md
/copilot-config.md
/copilot-prompt.md

# ChatGPT / OpenAI
/CHATGPT.md
/GPT.md
/OPENAI.md
/chatgpt-instructions.md
/gpt-instructions.md
/openai-instructions.md

# Generic AI/LLM instructions
/AI.md
/AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md
/LLM.md
/LLM_INSTRUCTIONS.md
/.ai-instructions.md
/.llm-instructions.md
/ai-prompt.md
/llm-prompt.md
/assistant-instructions.md

# Custom instructions directories
/.ai/
/.llm/
/.copilot/
/ai-instructions/
/llm-instructions/

# Claude Code. Personal config (settings.local.json and friends) stays private,
# but .claude/skills is project content -- it is the copy Claude Code actually
# reads, and the one .github/skills is meant to mirror. Ignoring the whole
# directory made that mirror unenforceable: the skills existed only in whoever's
# working tree wrote them, and a fresh clone got none of them.
#
# Must be "/.claude/*" and not "/.claude/": git does not descend into an excluded
# directory, so a negation under it would never be reached. Anchored with a
# leading "/" like everything else here, so template/.claude/ is untouched.
/.claude/*
!/.claude/skills/

# openspec installs its own skills and commands. They are tool state that openspec
# rewrites, not project content -- the same reason /.github/skills/openspec-*/ and
# /.github/prompts/ are ignored above.
/.claude/skills/openspec-*/

# Project-specific AI context (kept private)
/.cursorrules
/.cursor/
/.aider*
/.continue/
/openspec

# Git worktrees
/.worktrees/
